entry.title: [dPWA] Support uninstallation of individual install URLs for externally managed web apps
entry.content:
There was no code path for removing an install URL from an externally

managed web app. Instead we were removing the associated install

source entirely. This CL fixes that behavior.



WebAppUninstallCommand's queue processing has been converted into

a sequential async loop rather than a batch uninstall job starter.

This is for simpler reasoning about multiple async mutations.

Performance is not under consideration here as it is an uninstallation

action.



Bug: 1427340

entry.title: Add a high priority queue for sync cookie calls in the network service
entry.content:
This change adds a minimal scheduler for the network service thread

which has a default task queue and high priority task queue. The

RestrictedCookieManager interface will be bound using the high priority

task queue, which should make the sync cookie accesses/writes from the

renderer faster if there are other tasks that need to be run in the

network service.



The hope is that re-ordering these tasks with other network tasks will

not be a problem since they are generally called as sync calls from the

renderer. If there turns out to be problems with this later we can

revisit how tasks are prioritized.



Bug: 1448685

entry.title: [QT] Fix font double-scaling
entry.content:
The old logic was multiplying by the scale factor to convert points to

pixels. However, this caused a double-scaling issue where setting the

scale to 2x would result in a 4x font size increase. Additionally,

fonts at 1x were too small. The correct conversion ratio is 96/72,

which matches the logic used by GTK [1]. With this change, I've

verified the font size matches that of native QT applications when

testing in a KDE environment with several scale factors.



[1] https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:ui/gtk/gtk_ui.cc;drc=38f747321ad5e796f850046f43aa938fbfdf6fed;l=836

entry.title: Introduce new SinglePrefetch getters
entry.content:
`PrefetchContainer::GetSinglePrefetch()` depends on

`NoVarySearchHelper` (via `IsMatchingURL()`), but this

should be unnecessary because NVS matching is already

done elsewhere (e.g.

`PrefetchContainer::DoesCurrentURLToServeMatch()` called from

`PrefetchURLLoaderInterceptor::MaybeCreateLoader()`), and

should be avoided to reduce dependencies between

`PrefetchDocumentManager` and `PrefetchContainer`.



This CL introduces new SinglePrefetch getters that doesn't

depend on `NoVarySearchHelper`.

Basically we only need to access the current (and previous)

prefetching redirect reg ("ToPrefetch" methods), and

the current serving redirect reg ("ToServe" methods),

and subsequent CLs will replace `GetSinglePrefetch()` calls

with the new getters one by one, eventually removing

`GetSinglePrefetch()`.

entry.title: viz: Preserve root pass remapped ID when the surface ID changes
entry.content:
This change preserves the root render pass' remapped ID when a surface

is cloned with a new local surface ID (LSID).



We currently preserve damage (via prev_frame_index) in the case when a

surface is cloned with a new LSID. This works well for the root surface

the output device owns the root surface. However, when

renderer_allocates_images, then the root surface will appear as an

entry in SkiaRenderer::render_pass_backings_, which is a map keyed by

render pass ID. When the LSID changes, we could end up with a frame

that assumes that content from the previous frame is still present

(via preserved damage), but we have a new root pass ID.

entry.title: Exo: fix wrong pointer surface
entry.content:
When the surface size changes, the surface ID of the layer of the host

window of the exo pointer might not be updated yet when

RequestCopyOfOutput happens. This could cause the cursor have wrong

bitmap but with the correct size (when the size is smaller the bitmap

would look clipped).



Now we use host window's surface ID which is guaranteed updated to

send RequestCopyOfOutput request. Also apply the same scale to the

cursor bitmap which is resource_scale_factor/GetScaleFactor().

Also remove capture_scale_ since it is cancelled out during

the the chains of calculation.

entry.title: Fix out-of-bounds base::StringPiece handling in ash/ambient
entry.content:
A base::StringPiece is not guaranteed to end at a NUL character, unlike

a C string. Like a span or any other pointer/length tuple, it is always

a bug to call .data() without also calling .size(). With strings, it is

particularly risky because many functions will silently interpret a

single pointer as a NUL-terminated C string.



Two functions in ash/ambient made this mistake. IsFrameRateMarker was

only ever called on std::string, so it was fine.

ParseDynamicLottieAssetId is called more extensively, so I haven't

checked the whole call graph.



Unfortunately, due to RE2 and Chromium both forking the standard

std::string_view vocabulary type, the conversion is a bit tedious.

RE2 has since removed its fork. Updating that is tracked by

https://crbug.com/1447090. Fixing Chromium's behavior is tracked by

https://crbug.com/691162.



Until then, I've just made IsFrameRateMarker take a std::string

const-ref, as it's just a private function anyway. base::StringPiece

would be ideal, but so it goes. ParseDynamicLottieAssetId is used more

extensively, so I've decomposed it into data/size and recomposed it, but

left a TODO that we can clean this up later. Likely there will be a lot

of re2::StringPiece cleanups we can do.



Bug: 1447090, 691162

entry.title: [GridNG] Allow fixed inline size in CreateConstraintSpaceForMeasure
entry.content:
1. Before subgrid, whenever a grid item's constraint space for measure

had an indefinite available inline size it meant that the item was

orthogonal and we were at the first column sizing step.



However, this is not true anymore since a subgrid can size its rows

before its columns are resolved. This CL fixes such expectation in

`NGGridLayoutAlgorithm::ContributionSizeForGridItem`.



2. Re-enabling the `orthogonal-writing-mode-002.html` WPT test.
